# TTD architecture

## Layering

- **`ttd.core`** — pure domain logic: rollup, rounding, money, slugs, errors (no I/O)
- **`ttd.services`** — async application services orchestrating storage + core
- **`ttd.storage`** — ferro-orm models and DB lifecycle
- **`ttd.parsing` / `ttd.invoicing` / `ttd.interchange` / `ttd.reporting`** — focused capability packages used by services and surfaces
- **`ttd.cli` / `ttd.tui`** — thin adapters only: parse input → `await` services → format output

Never implement domain rules, rounding, or persistence in surface packages.

## Async

- Services and DB access are `async`
- CLI uses cyclopts async commands; TUI calls async services from Textual async hooks

